, of course. But, her basis does not compel her conclusion, given the natural and inevitable opposite problem: As with every collective system that criminalizes the individual's natural rights AS an individual, incentives for improvement from within become drown by the bureaucratic denial of individual opportunity for whatever kinds of natural individual differentiations that the bureaucracy sees fit to resist, oppose, and punish. If only we all were clones, THEN this woman's logic just might work---until, that is, the grossly unintelligent mono-culture of clones collapses by one or more biological epidemics. The last time I checked, Mom Nature much prefers natural individual differentiation over either imposed 'cloning' or some hypothetical natural cloning. This woman's monotonous direction for improvement is as bad as anything can get, by looking for some salvific solution in The Divine Right of Bureaucratic/Collective Hosanna. The only sane foundation for collective action is individual rights and individual needs, in that order. This woman have us murder our individual rights on the alter of some kind of abstract collective need. &quot;I got married&quot;, said Spock's father, &quot;to a human woman not because I loved her, but simply because it seemed the logical thing to do at the time.&quot; But, then, at least, we can say, he got married to an individual woman, and not to a collective harem of angry nags. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1724" language="en" documentId="2657" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Daniel1212360" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:32PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="6" thumbsDown="0" origId="2657" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1724"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>